{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Rows with missing required fields are rejected and appear in the dead-letter queue with the original row number.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure risk is in module handoff: CSV parser must preserve row index, validator must reject, and DLQ writer must carry original metadata. A unit test of validator alone can miss row-number propagation bugs.","test_description":"Run pipeline components together on a small CSV fixture with missing required fields. Assert invalid rows are not sent to normalize/write path and are emitted to a test DLQ sink with exact original CSV row numbers.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The transformation correctly converts date strings in multiple formats (ISO 8601, US, European) to a single canonical format.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Core failure boundary is date parsing/normalization logic in a deterministic transform function. No I/O or external system is required to catch real format-conversion errors.","test_description":"Table-driven tests for transform function with ISO 8601, US, and European date inputs (plus ambiguous/invalid edge cases) asserting canonical output format and explicit failure behavior where applicable.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.74,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A CSV file with 500,000 rows completes processing within the configured timeout without running out of memory.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real runtime memory behavior, process limits, and timeout behavior under load. In-process mocks cannot reliably surface OOM/GC/throughput failures.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline as a real process against a generated 500k-row CSV and